author: COMSOL
description: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) is a common technique in which a small oscillating perturbation is applied to an electrochemical system to interrogate kinetic and transport properties. This example models EIS for a range of electrode reaction rates. Nyquist and Bode plots illustrate the transition between the reaction proceeding under kinetic or transport control.
